micropython setup guide:

1. Download Thonny here: https://thonny.org/
2. Download Firmware file for RPi Pico: https://www.raspberrypi.org/documentation/rp2040/getting-started/#getting-started-with-micropython
3. Scroll down and click on "Getting Started, MicroPython" and download the UF2 file
4. plug in RPi while holding the boot button down, let go after you have plugged into the pc
5. Open Thonny
6. Click on Run > Select Interpreter > select micropython (raspberry pi pico)
7. New File > select raspberry pi pico

